cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with cross-lingual word embeddings and their alignment. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a self-supervised method for refining the alignment of unsupervised bilingual word embeddings. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques. The paper also mentions the use of center-invariance, which is a common technique in computer vision, so it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Finally, the paper proposes a method for aligning cross-lingual embeddings, which could fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
